注音/拼音音譯的盲文字母 ㄍ ''g'' ({{IPA|/k/}})，ㄘ ''c'' ({{IPA|/tsʰ/}})，及 ㄙ ''s'' ({{IPA|/s/}})可以替代[[龈腭音|龈腭音]] ㄐ ''j'' ({{IPA|/tɕ/}})，ㄑ ''q'' ({{IPA|/tɕʰ/}})，及 ㄒ ''x'' ({{IPA|/ɕ/}})。即《ㄍ與ㄐ》；《ㄑ與ㄘ》；《ㄙ與ㄒ》三組的點字符號相同，但使用時並不會造成混淆。 而後者〈j、q、x〉可接"[[閉前不圓唇元音|閉前不圓唇元音]]"〈ㄧ ''i'' ({{IPA|/i/}})〉與"[[閉前圓唇元音|閉前圓唇元音]]"〈ㄩ ''ü'' ({{IPA|/y/}})〉之結合韻；例如：'''ㄍ'''＋'''ㄢ''' 點字爲（{{Braille cell|type=6dot|size=12px|k}}{{Braille cell|type=6dot|size=12px|v}}）ㄍㄢ；'''ㄐ'''＋'''ㄧㄢ''' 點字爲（{{Braille cell|type=6dot|size=12px|k}}{{Braille cell|type=6dot|size=12px|t}}）ㄐㄧㄢ，所以在注音和拼音裡的 ''g, c, s'' 及 ''j, q, x'' 語言之間的區別是多餘的。<ref>[sic] One might expect ㄐ ''j'' ({{IPA|/tɕ/}}) to pair with ㄗ ''z'' ({{IPA|/ts/}}), by analogy with the others. Compare [http://www.nise.go.jp/research/kogaku/twatanab/Tactile/WorldBraille/TaiwanBrailleBook.jpg here], where the character 學 ''xué'' is rendered {{Braille cell|⠑|⠦|⠂}} "süé".  Historically it could have been either.  The principal behind the assignments seems to be that, of the historically appropriate pairs of letters ''g~z, k~c,'' and ''h~s'', the letter with the fewer dots is used for ''j, q, x''.</ref>

